    """ Filter given list of any python values only for integers
    >>> filter_integers(['a', 3.14, 5])
    [5]
    >>> filter_integers([1, 2, 3, 'abc', {}, []])
    [1, 2, 3]
    """
    if not values:
        return []
    nums = {i: v for i, v in enumerate(values) if isinstance(v, int)}
    if not nums:
        return values
    return [v for v in values if v in nums]
